race.comment: DIRECT FIRE (1) was left in front a long way from home and couldn't hold out TOM CRUISING and one other in the closing stages over 1500m here last start. Cherry ripe now after four runs back and is going to be difficult to run down. HARDPOINT (3) raced handy and gave a good kick but was edged out when resuming over 1400m here back on 27 September. Trialled since then at Hawkesbury to keep him up to the mark. Good second-up performer who loves this trip and races well at Kembla. Big chance to go one better. WINNING POINT (4) travelled midfield but probably found 1400m a bit sharp when second-up here recently. Should be getting close to her peak, particularly over an extra furlong this time. MISS HVAR (7) was ridden closer to the speed last start and responded by scoring a soft win over 1500m at Hawkesbury. Can hold that form at just the fourth run back. TOM CRUISING (9) caused an upset winning here over 1500m recently. In the mix again.
